## Conventions

**Code style:**
- Python: Black formatter, 88 char line length, isort for imports
- TypeScript: Prettier, 2-space indent, single quotes
- No `any` types in TypeScript without a comment explaining why

**Naming:**
- Functions: `snake_case`
- Classes: `PascalCase`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Files: `kebab-case.ts` (frontend), `snake_case.py` (backend)

**Testing:**
- Every new service method needs a unit test
- New API endpoints need integration tests
- Test files mirror the source tree: `tests/unit/services/test_user_service.py`

**Commits:**
- Conventional commits format: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`
- One logical change per commit

---

## Rules

**Do:**
- Check existing patterns before implementing something new
- Use the existing helper utilities in `src/utils/` before writing new ones
- Add type hints to all Python functions
- Run `make lint` and `make test` before completing any task

**Do not:**
- Modify database migration files that have already been applied (`migrations/versions/`)
- Change authentication or authorization logic without explicitly flagging it for review
- Add new dependencies without noting them (add to requirements.txt / package.json and flag in your response)
- Hard-code credentials, API keys, or environment-specific values
- Write to production databases directly (use the dev environment)

**When uncertain:**
- Ask before making changes to shared utilities or base classes
- Flag any change that affects more than 3 files for review before proceeding
- Do not guess at business logic requirements — ask

---

## Tool Access

**Allowed:**
- Read all files in this repository
- Write to `src/`, `tests/`, `frontend/src/`
- Run `make test`, `make lint`, `pytest`, `npm test`
- Execute read-only database queries in the dev environment

**Not allowed:**
- Push to `main` branch directly
- Modify CI/CD configuration without explicit instruction
- Execute database migrations without confirmation
- Access credentials files (`.env`, `secrets/`)

---

## Out of Scope

The following are outside the scope of this agent unless explicitly instructed:
- Infrastructure changes (Terraform, Docker Compose, Nginx config)
- Third-party service configuration (AWS, Stripe, SendGrid)
- Billing or payment logic
- User data deletion or bulk data operations
